The paper deals with the problem of scientific image tampering detection, which involves computer vision and image processing techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of image integrity and manipulation, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for detecting image tampering, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
